    <h1>Denmark immigration fiscal impact: official Ministry of Finance data</h1>
    <p class="intro">Denmark's Finance Ministry (Finansministeriet) publishes the most comprehensive official accounting of immigration's net fiscal effect in Europe. The 2023 figure: −DKK 16bn/year for all immigrants and descendants combined. The breakdown by origin reverses the sign entirely.</p>
    <div class="lang-switch"><a href="/faq/danemark-fiscalite-immigration/">🌐 日本語版</a></div>
  </div>

  <section>
    <h2>Key figures (Finansministeriet 2023)</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Group</th><th>Net fiscal balance (annual)</th><th>Source</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>All immigrants &amp; descendants</strong></td>
          <td><strong>−DKK 16bn/year</strong></td>
          <td><a href="https://www.fm.dk" rel="noopener">Finansministeriet 2023</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Non-Western immigrants &amp; descendants</td>
          <td>−DKK 27bn/year (net cost)</td>
          <td>Finansministeriet 2023</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Western immigrants &amp; descendants</td>
          <td>+DKK 11bn/year (net contribution)</td>
          <td>Finansministeriet 2023</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Reference year</td>
          <td>2019 data (revised September 2023)</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What this means</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>The −DKK 16bn aggregate is an average across all immigrants</strong>. It masks a sign reversal between Western and non-Western immigrants. Western immigrants (EU, North America, Australia) contribute +DKK 11bn; non-Western immigrants cost −DKK 27bn.</li>
      <li><strong>Fiscal outcome depends heavily on immigration motive.</strong> Labour migrants generally produce positive contributions; refugees and family reunification migrants produce net costs — a pattern documented across all Nordic countries.</li>
      <li>Finansministeriet uses a <strong>static model</strong> measuring current-year tax and benefit flows. It does not project lifetime contributions, descendants' economic effects, or long-run GDP impacts.</li>
      <li>Denmark is <strong>one of the most transparent countries in the world</strong> for this type of accounting. Equivalent official estimates are published only by Norway (SSB) and Germany (Ifo/IAB) among Western countries.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

